               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260914-388-person2020">
                  JOHN 
                  CULLIFORD
               <interp inst="t18260914-388-person2020" type="surname" value="CULLIFORD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-388-person2020" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-388-person2020" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman. I met the prisoner in Lisle-street, Leicester-square, on the 1st of June, at half-past two o'clock in the morning, with a bag under his arm - he looked at me, and went on into Little Newport-street - I went up to him and said, "I think you have got something that is not all right;" he threw it at me - I caught it in my arms - it contained this glass; he ran off; but was not a quarter of an hour out of my sight - I gave the alarm, and he was taken.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260914-388-person2021">
