            . I am a constable. I was at the watch-house, and received him in charge.</p>
               <p>HENRY BINGHAM. I live in <placeName id="t18260914-388-crimeloc2174">Ryder's-court</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18260914-388-crimeloc2174" type="placeName" value="Ryder's-court"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18260914-388-crimeloc2174" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260914-388-off2172 t18260914-388-crimeloc2174"></join>. These pieces of glass are mine, and worth about 1l.; they were in a cupboard, in a lumber-room.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. They were given to me by a man to carry - Mr. Bingham told my mother that if I wanted to get released, I had better say who he was - I did so; it was Phillips, who I went to to sell my coat - he sent a boy with me, who brought the property out.</p>
               <p>HENRY BINGHAM. He said Phillips, a Jew, instigated<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182609140150"></xptr>him to carry them - I said I knew several persons of that name, and he had better produce the man.</p>
